Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.04,0:00:11.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I see that you are awake,\NSlaine Troyard.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.17,0:00:14.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Where am I...?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.29,0:00:19.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,My castle. You are safe now.\NTake your time and rest.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.92,0:00:21.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What happened...?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.30,0:00:26.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I remember being interrogated\Nby Count Cruhteo, but then...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.97,0:00:31.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You have nothing to fear.\NI have dealt with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.44,0:00:36.31,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The count... is dead?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.52,0:00:43.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I am indebted to your father. Hence,\NI am obligated to repay that debt.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.66,0:00:46.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Indebted?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.20,0:00:52.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,When war first broke out 15 years ago,\NI came down to Earth as a scout.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.04,0:00:57.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,There, I was caught in Heaven's Fall\Nand was mortally wounded.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.67,0:01:02.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Amidst that cataclysm where\Nthe Moon was sundered,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.13,0:01:05.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,the Earth's crust deformed, and there\Nwas nowhere to turn for help,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.64,0:01:11.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I was found by your father,\NDr. Troyard, and he saved my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.39,0:01:13.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Father did that?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.60,0:01:18.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I have seen clearly the depths\Nof your loyalty to the princess.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.61,0:01:24.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Your devotion in concealing her survival so\Nas not to alert the assassins is admirable.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.74,0:01:28.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,How did you know\Nthat she...?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.66,0:01:32.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Count Cruhteo is no traitor.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.58,0:01:36.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Quite the contrary, he is a true knight\Nwho has sworn fealty to the princess.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.54,0:01:44.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,While I am the traitor who\Nplotted her assassination.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.85,0:03:24.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Pay close attention to your surroundings.\NCome on, infrared, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.90,0:03:26.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Keep your guard up.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.23,0:03:30.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, ma'am! Three aircraft,\N2 o'clock! No IFF signal!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.61,0:03:33.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Flagging as hostiles! Almost in\Neffective weapons range!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.41,0:03:34.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Now engaging!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.25,0:03:43.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Wow, Inko's good.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.42,0:03:47.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,She has pretty good instincts.\NYou here to practice, too, Calm?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.84,0:03:50.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I got assigned\Nto maintenance crew.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.80,0:03:52.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,For now, maybe.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.80,0:03:55.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You mean there might\Nbe an opening?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.89,0:03:58.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This is war, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.35,0:04:02.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Let me try.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.90,0:04:06.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Sniper Girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.52,0:04:09.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But I thought you hadn't\Nhad any military training.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.15,0:04:10.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I learned from games.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.36,0:04:14.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Sim-Kat 10, you mean?\NThat's such a solid game...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.91,0:04:18.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm only so-so in live drills,\Nbut I kick ass on that game.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.91,0:04:22.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Man, I'm amazed you learned to pilot\Nthe real thing from a game...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.05,0:04:30.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The Martians, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.38,0:04:36.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,They look exactly the same as us Terrans, huh?\NYou'd never know unless somebody told you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.18,0:04:43.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Inaho's such a jerk. He knew who she\Nreally was, but didn't tell us.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.06,0:04:46.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,My Nao has grown up, I guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.73,0:04:49.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I just wish that he had opened up\Nto his big sister, at least.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.69,0:04:52.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Since he met a girl\Nhe likes, and all...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.32,0:04:54.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Come again?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.28,0:04:55.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}What's that supposed\Nto mean?!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.53,0:04:59.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Given the times we live in, a Martian\Nwon't be met with open arms,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.87,0:05:05.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,but if he marries a princess, my little Nao\Nwould be marrying into serious money!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.17,0:05:08.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Is that true?!\NIs that what he'll do?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.59,0:05:10.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I don't get that vibe at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.21,0:05:15.89,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,He never cracks a smile, and he has the\Nsame old grumpy look on his face..
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.89,0:05:17.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's totally different.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.85,0:05:19.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.18,0:05:21.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm family, so I can tell.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.68,0:05:24.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I know how he looks when\Nhe's happy, when he's depressed,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.73,0:05:26.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and when he's lying.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.81,0:05:29.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That is his "I'm on\Ncloud nine" face.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.61,0:05:30.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I dunno...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.98,0:05:36.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,For starters, that cold fish listening intently\Nto a girl is unusual in and of itself, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.57,0:05:37.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Now that is true!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.78,0:05:40.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,For that boy, it's the ultimate\Nexpression of affection.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.83,0:05:45.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Warrant Officer Kaizuka!\NMay I take a break?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.08,0:05:45.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.90,0:05:47.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Me, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.09,0:05:51.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,May I use the simulator?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.59,0:05:56.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Sure, of course.\NYou don't want to join them?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.35,0:06:02.89,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Can you really tell?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.31,0:06:07.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,When someone is lying?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.10,0:06:12.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Pretty much. I mean, I can tell\Nfrom your face that you're lying.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.36,0:06:14.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,A Martian!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.74,0:06:18.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And a princess, to boot!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.28,0:06:21.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Guys sure love to try to\Ntackle a challenge, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.74,0:06:25.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But you have a shot, too,\Nso don't give up. Hang in there.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.00,0:06:29.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,As a big sister, I love that my little\Nbrother is so popular with the girls.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.79,0:06:33.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,These are the 26 Landing\NCastle drop points
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.92,0:06:36.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,confirmed before contact\Nwas lost with our main force.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.22,0:06:41.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,However, the Mars Knights\Nconsists of 37 Clans.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.14,0:06:44.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,There is a possibility that other\NLanding Castles have come down.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.06,0:06:47.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Given what we've seen,\Nthere is a possibility
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.48,0:06:49.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,that their invasion has\Nextended to urban areas.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.90,0:06:53.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Therefore, we can minimize the\Npossibility of enemy encounters
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.27,0:06:56.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,by plotting a route through low\Npopulation density areas,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.15,0:06:58.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,avoiding radar, and flying\Nat low altitude.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.82,0:07:01.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Mizusaki.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.79,0:07:02.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Ma'am?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.99,0:07:05.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Would you like to know\Nwhy you can't get a date?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.87,0:07:09.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Possibility, possibility, possibility...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.25,0:07:15.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If you do nothing but play it safe,\Nyou'll never bump into Mr. Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.96,0:07:19.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I was given to understand that one\Nshould form a bond first, ma'am.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.22,0:07:23.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,All right, let's go with your "I want to\Nmake steady progress towards my goal,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.05,0:07:25.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,even if means holding my nose"\Nsort of operation.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.97,0:07:27.39,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You don't approve?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.64,0:07:31.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No, I think it's\Na very simple operation.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.49,0:07:40.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,She doesn't approve...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.87,0:07:48.25,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Target destroyed.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.25,0:07:51.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Okay, simulation complete.\N"Rayet," right?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.58,0:07:55.17,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}You've got some skills.\NGamers are a formidable bunch.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.25,0:07:56.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Increase the difficulty.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.76,0:08:00.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe we should call it a day.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.55,0:08:02.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'm fine, keep going.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.22,0:08:07.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, then. Why don't I throw in\Nsomething we fought recently?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.06,0:08:09.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Try this.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.98,0:08:11.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Beginning simulation.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.44,0:08:16.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Thermal signature detected.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.94,0:08:19.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Off my 10 o'clock.\NAlmost in effective range.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.84,0:08:45.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Don't do that, Rayet.\NThe gun barrel will overheat.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.89,0:08:52.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Simulation complete.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.44,0:08:55.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry. I made it too\Nhard all of a sudden.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.27,0:08:57.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Did it throw you?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.69,0:09:00.81,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Warrant Officer Kaizuka.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.81,0:09:01.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Dr. Yagarai.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.20,0:09:04.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,How is the exoskeleton working?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.74,0:09:06.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Wanna arm wrestle?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.35,0:09:07.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks, but no.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.95,0:09:11.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Actually, would you mind if I borrowed\Nyour simulator program later?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.12,0:09:14.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You joining the fight, Doc?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.79,0:09:17.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No, it's not for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.38,0:09:20.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I need it for treatment.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.51,0:09:25.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.26,0:09:29.89,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I can't believe our captain turned out\Nto be your kid sister, Humeray.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.06,0:09:38.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Probably explains where\Nshe gets her guts from.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.21,0:09:58.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Rayet.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.09,0:10:02.09,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,May I join you?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.76,0:10:07.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Suit yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.18,0:10:14.89,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Terran food is most delicious. So many\Nunusual dishes not found on Vers.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.23,0:10:18.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Is that optical camouflage, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.61,0:10:23.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No, Inaho's friend Nina was kind enough\Nto allow me to borrow these.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.40,0:10:27.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,She thought it might be difficult to\Nwalk in a cramped ship in that dress.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.62,0:10:31.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't she kind?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.83,0:10:36.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Highness, this is for you!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.96,0:10:41.17,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,How lovely!\NA papercraft Terran bird!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.67,0:10:44.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you, I shall treasure it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.34,0:10:47.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That was most thoughtful\Nof you, commoner.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.76,0:10:50.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,When there is peace between\NEarth and Vers,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.55,0:10:52.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,we shall speak of this to\NHis Imperial Majesty, and-
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.35,0:10:57.39,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.98,0:11:02.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Why did you reveal your identity?\NMartians are seen as the enemy.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.65,0:11:06.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,How can you be so\Ncalm and composed?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.28,0:11:08.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Even though you were\Nbetrayed by Martians...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.24,0:11:12.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You're crazy, lady.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.41,0:11:15.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Mind your tongue! How dare you say\Nsuch a thing to Her Highness?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.75,0:11:18.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You thought they were\Nyour friends...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.83,0:11:21.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, come back here!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.09,0:11:24.17,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This is the problem with Terrans!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.84,0:11:30.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,How do you feel?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.64,0:11:33.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No problem. I'm fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.30,0:11:36.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I recreated the scene based on\Nyour descriptions, Lt. Marito.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.85,0:11:40.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It ought to be close, but if I got\Nsomething wrong, please tell me.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.69,0:11:43.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Is this really going to help?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.06,0:11:44.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,PTSD...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.40,0:11:49.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,One treatment for post-traumatic\Nstress disorder is to
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.57,0:11:54.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,recreate the incident that caused it\Nand to relive it again and again.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.53,0:11:58.75,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Relive a terrifying experience often enough\Nand you get acclimated to it, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.71,0:12:01.75,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We'll just have to see.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.92,0:12:03.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Let's begin.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.50,0:12:06.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Fine, whatever...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.30,0:12:09.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,All right, here we go.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.68,0:12:16.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, come on... Even games are more\Nrealistic than this these days.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.68,0:12:19.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, are they?\NBut we aren't playing a game.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.48,0:12:22.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Uh, this street is flipped.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.56,0:12:24.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'll fix that for next time.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.02,0:12:28.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What's that down there?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.23,0:12:30.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's Humeray, your war buddy.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.53,0:12:35.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Give me a break. This blocky guy\Nain't what's bothering me!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.62,0:12:38.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Trust me. Just be quiet\Nand watch.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.83,0:12:41.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Come off it... Are you\Nmessing with me?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.13,0:12:47.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell?! That's-
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.30,0:12:51.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Marito!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.09,0:12:56.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell is that?! Nobody said\Nthere was something like that here!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.30,0:12:58.93,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be scared!\NWe outnumber them!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.10,0:13:01.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Platoon Commander to all tanks!\NPiecemeal attack!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.65,0:13:05.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What the...?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.53,0:13:09.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Marito!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.11,0:13:13.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That thing's doing this?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.41,0:13:18.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's flying?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.75,0:13:23.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Our shells, they-
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.04,0:13:23.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Marito!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.87,0:13:26.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Anti-gravity? No...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.60,0:13:45.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This tank is a lost cause.\NWe're bailing, Humeray!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.56,0:13:46.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I can't...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.98,0:13:48.67,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,My legs are pinned!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.65,0:13:50.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.32,0:13:51.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Humeray!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.11,0:13:53.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Marito! Get me out, Marito!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.03,0:13:59.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Marito! Marito!\NHurry, Marito!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.37,0:14:07.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Marito! Shoot me!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.33,0:14:08.75,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Please! Marito!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.75,0:14:11.09,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry! Hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.42,0:14:13.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Shoot me! Marito!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.63,0:14:51.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Lieutenant! Lt. Marito!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.00,0:14:53.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Are you all right, Lieutenant?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.59,0:14:58.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Everything you saw\Nis in the past.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.05,0:15:02.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You're safe now.\NThis isn't Tanegashima.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.02,0:15:09.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Like hell we are...\NThis is a battlefield now, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.02,0:15:14.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I think that's enough\Nfor today.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.28,0:15:20.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Talk about pathetic... Being scared\Nof that blocky thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.62,0:15:24.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No, that isn't what\Nyou are afraid of.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.37,0:15:30.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's the fact that you\Nkilled your friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.81,0:15:52.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}This is crazy, this is crazy,\Nthis is crazy...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.11,0:15:55.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}This is so crazy!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.74,0:16:05.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Why did she reveal her identity?\NWhy is she so calm?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.99,0:16:11.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Why? Why? Why?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.54,0:16:16.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Why... is she...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.93,0:16:24.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Why... am I...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.32,0:16:38.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What is the matter?\NNot hungry?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.36,0:16:42.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Do not worry,\Nit is not poisoned.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.78,0:16:46.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Had I wished to kill you,\NI would have done so long ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.54,0:16:49.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Milord...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.00,0:16:51.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.33,0:16:54.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you so determined\Nto fight Earth?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.96,0:17:00.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It is a lord's duty to his vassals\Nto fight to expand his territory.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.97,0:17:03.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Just for that?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.64,0:17:05.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It is that great a cause.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.47,0:17:09.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,These are creatures that fly\Nthrough the air, I understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.77,0:17:10.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, Milord.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.85,0:17:13.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, actually, this type\Nof bird is flightless.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.15,0:17:17.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Unimaginable luxury to\Nthe people of Vers,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.86,0:17:20.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,who subsist on\Nchlorella and krill.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.61,0:17:23.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I feel nothing but indignation\Ntowards the Terrans who
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.78,0:17:26.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,so offhandedly sent them\Nas relief supplies.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.41,0:17:32.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This is not a luxury item.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.46,0:17:35.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It is processed food tailored for\Nspace transport and preservation.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.79,0:17:37.63,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Culture is the sole\Ndomain of Earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.63,0:17:41.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,blessed with abundant water and air,\N overflowing with countless living creatures.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.22,0:17:46.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,On Father Vers, although technology\Nis advanced thanks to Aldnoah,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.18,0:17:49.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,culture has not\Ndeveloped at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.68,0:17:53.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,There is no reason that we should not seize\Nthis world and its plentiful resources.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.85,0:17:57.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But even so, surely there is no need\Nto exploit Princess Asseylum to-
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.44,0:18:01.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It is too late.\NThe war has already begun.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.28,0:18:04.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Her Highness will be\Na human sacrifice.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.36,0:18:05.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,She is innocent!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.86,0:18:10.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,She is royalty.\NHer very lineage is her crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.08,0:18:15.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Fifteen years ago, the royal family whipped the\Nknights into a frenzy and sent them against Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.08,0:18:19.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,For that, I will make them pay\Nwith their own flesh and blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.26,0:18:26.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Please don't kill her.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.26,0:18:30.81,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We are a people oppressed under a feudal\Nsystem centered around Aldnoah.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.43,0:18:36.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Our impoverished, shabby country looks with\Nscorn upon a world with a vast history.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.94,0:18:39.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Such nonsense...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.65,0:18:42.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It is only natural that Vers, where the masses\Nhad been controlled by saying,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.98,0:18:46.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,"Be envious of Earth, be jealous\Nof Earth, despise Earth,"
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.61,0:18:51.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,is so corrupt that only through invading\NEarth can its great cause be maintained.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.58,0:18:56.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Your injuries attest\Nto that all too well.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.50,0:19:02.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The royal family chose war.\NTo maintain order on Vers.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.84,0:19:07.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And then... Heaven's Fall came about\Nas a result of that war,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.51,0:19:10.89,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and my betrothed, Orlane,\Nlost her life!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.73,0:19:21.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This war is my vengeance.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.44,0:19:25.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This war is my appointed task.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.70,0:19:37.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Defy me, and I will show you no mercy. Even if\Nyou are the son of the man I owe my life to.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.04,0:19:47.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I was worried that they would be more hostile\Ntowards us, but it was for nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.22,0:19:50.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I am relieved that the\Npeople of Earth are so kind.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.51,0:19:54.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,They must understand that you are not\Ntheir enemy, but rather a victim.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.89,0:19:57.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Deep down, we are all\Nfellow human beings.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.35,0:20:00.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Though our places of birth may differ,\Nwe are capable of mutual understanding.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.69,0:20:03.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Some of them are rude\Nand strange, though...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.90,0:20:07.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, my apologies!\NI forgot your new clothing!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.24,0:20:08.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'll go fetch it at once!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.52,0:20:43.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, that was fast, Eddelri...ttsuo?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.27,0:21:28.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Shouldn't you be\Nwith Seylum?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.36,0:21:31.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Her name is not "Seylum"!\NIt is Her Royal Highness Asseylum!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.53,0:21:35.39,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Aldnoah drive, output falling!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.39,0:21:37.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Switch to auxiliary power!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.03,0:21:38.49,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Unable to maintain altitude!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.49,0:21:41.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Rate of descent increasing!\NImpact in 30 seconds!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.96,0:21:43.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,All hands, brace for impact!
